{"alignment_id": "shijing__guofeng-beifeng-005__002__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sheking-1871-ocr", "work_id": "shijing", "section_id": "guofeng-beifeng-005", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 0.99, "order": 2, "section_unit": "poem", "segment_type": "stanza", "alignment_granularity": "stanza", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "詩經·國風·邶風·005.2", "chinese_text": "終風且霾，惠然肯來，莫往莫來，悠悠我思。", "translation_ref": "Chung fung..2", "translation_text": "The wind blows, with clouds of dust.\nKindly he seems to be willing to come to me;\n[But] he neither goes nor comes.\nLong, long, do I think of him."}
{"alignment_id": "shijing__guofeng-beifeng-005__003__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sheking-1871-ocr", "work_id": "shijing", "section_id": "guofeng-beifeng-005", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 0.99, "order": 3, "section_unit": "poem", "segment_type": "stanza", "alignment_granularity": "stanza", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "詩經·國風·邶風·005.3", "chinese_text": "終風且曀，不日有曀，寤言不寐，願言則嚏。", "translation_ref": "Chung fung..3", "translation_text": "The wind blew, and the sky was cloudy;\nBefore a day elapses, it is cloudy again.\nI awake, and cannot sleep;\nI think of him, and gasp."}
{"alignment_id": "shijing__guofeng-beifeng-005__004__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sheking-1871-ocr", "work_id": "shijing", "section_id": "guofeng-beifeng-005", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 0.99, "order": 4, "section_unit": "poem", "segment_type": "stanza", "alignment_granularity": "stanza", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "詩經·國風·邶風·005.4", "chinese_text": "曀曀其陰，虺虺其靁，寤言不寐，願言則懷。", "translation_ref": "Chung fung..4", "translation_text": "All cloudy is the darkness,\nAnd the thunder keeps muttering.\nI awake and cannot sleep;\nI think of him, and my breast is full of pain."}
